EXTRACTED VALUE: Although everything is not perfect in Soulcalibur IV it is still one of those games that every 360 owner should have in their collection.
The whole is deep, compelling, personal and capable of so much incidental humour and charm.
Not quite as special as the original, but still impossible to ignore.
You may get a sense of deja vu as you play, but GRAW 2 is still a game that's worth having in your library. [May 2007, p.52]
Prey is unique and bizarre, and at the same time familiar. If you enjoy future themed shooters you're going to love the ride the Prey provides.
It provides plenty of glorious visuals, the audio is top-notch and the missions are pretty damn fun.
The Darkness is truly a brilliant ray of light during this otherwise abysmal summer gaming drought.
